name: UInterchangeBaseNodeContainer
doc:
The Interchange UInterchangeBaseNode graph is a format used to feed factories and writers when they import, reimport, and
export an asset or scene.

This container holds a flat list of all nodes that have been translated from the source data.
Translators fill this container, and the import/export managers read it to execute the import/export process.

methods.name: AddNode
ComputeChildrenCache
methods.doc: Fill the cache of children UIDs to optimize the GetNodeChildrenUids call.

methods.name: GetNode
methods.doc: Get a node pointer. Once added to the container, nodes are considered const.

methods.name: GetNodeChildren
methods.doc: Get the nth const child of the node

methods.name: GetNodeChildrenCount
methods.doc: Get the number of children the node has.

methods.name: GetNodeChildrenUids
methods.doc: Get the UIDs of all the node's children.

methods.name: GetNodes
methods.doc: Return all nodes that are of the ClassNode type.

methods.name: GetRoots
methods.doc: Return all nodes that do not have any parent.

methods.name: IsNodeUidValid
methods.doc: Return true if the node unique ID exists in the container.

methods.name: LoadFromFile
methods.doc: Serialize the node container from the specified file.

methods.name: ResetChildrenCache
methods.doc: Reset the cache of children UIDs.

methods.name: SaveToFile
methods.doc: Serialize the node container into the specified file.

methods.name: SetNodeParentUid
methods.doc: Set the ParentUid of the node.
